    "top_event": "Uncontrolled release of energy and tool ejection from wellbore",
    "incident_type": "Equipment failure",
    "costs": "4000",
    "actions_taken": [
      "Pre-job safety meeting held",
      "Barricades erected on cellar and wellbay decks",
      "All non-essential personnel cleared from area",
      "Safety stand down called",
      "Onsite investigation initiated",
      "BSEE onsite investigation conducted on 2023-02-03"
    ],
    "summary": "On January 31, 2023, during temporary abandonment of the E-4 well at Ship Shoal 224 E platform, a wireline casing cutter operation resulted in uncontrolled release of trapped pressure in the annulus below a subsea wellhead tieback system. The tool string and fluids were ejected from the wellbore, damaging grating on the cellar and wellbay decks. No injuries were reported. The root cause was that personnel were unaware of trapped pressure in the 10-3/8\" and 7-5/8\" annulus due to lack of communication above and below the subsea wellhead system and absence of pressure control equipment.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Install slip-on surface wellhead on all wells with subsea wellhead systems at the facility",
      "Update standard operating procedures to include utilizing pressure control equipment before perforating untested annuli"
    ],
    "key_phrases": [
      "trapped pressure",
      "subsea wellhead tieback system",
      "wireline casing cutter",
      "tool string ejection",
      "lack of communication",
      "pressure control equipment"
    ]
  },
